    "To view a copy of this licence, visit http://creativecommons.",
    "org/licenses/by/4.0/.",
    "A glance of plausible Aristotelian and Wittgensteinian views of moral competence discloses a large role for moral sensitivity, that is, an uncodified, practical skill to perceive which features of decision situations are morally relevant, and how they are relevant.",
    "Neither top-down nor bottom-up AMAs seem capable of fully attaining, or simulating, this sensitivity.",
    "Top-down AMAs are, by their nature, too rigid to appreciate all the aspects of our world and our fellow humans in it that, in varying situations, strike us as important to our moral decisions."
  ]
}